results.name: Decimal expansion of constant equal to concatenated nonprimes.
comment: A theorem of Copeland & Erdős proves that this constant is 10-normal. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Feb 06 2015
link: Demi Allen, Sky Brewer, Distribution Of Sequences Generated By Certain Simply-Constructed Normal Numbers, arXiv:1511.01789 [math.NT], 2015.
A. H. Copeland and P. Erdős, Note on normal numbers, Bull. Amer. Math. Soc. 52 (1946), pp. 857-860.
